en_146653_0	The Ministry of Transport has decided to deploy civil security officials at unprotected railway crossings.
en_146653_1	This is due to the ongoing strike that was lunched by unprotected railway crossing operators demanding a salary increase.
en_146653_2	Minister of Transport and Civil Aviation Nimal Siripala de Silva said there are a total of 676 such gates across the island and 25 per cent of the operators are on strike.
en_146653_3	He also said that automatic traffic lights will be set up in 200 of these gates.
